data.meta_description: William Williams (July 18, 1800 – 1878) was the first Anglican Bishop of Waiapu and the father and grandfather of two others. He published an early dictionary and grammar of the Mâori language. [edit] Biography Williams was born in Nottingham to Thomas and Mary Williams. William initially trained as a surgeon but...
